A man identified as Samuel Arunsi Eze was on Saturday, 25th February, reportedly beheaded by a political thug known as Daniel Mgba during the electoral violence in the Ndi Agwu community of Abam, Arochukwu Local Government Area of Abia State. According to eyewitnesses, two individuals lost their lives in the course of the ongoing general election. Confirming the gruesome incident, eyewitnesses noted the need for peaceful conduct during the electoral process as the second person involved in the incident was also reportedly killed, Tribune reported. The incident has sparked widespread condemnation and calls for thorough investigation and justice for the victims.